<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 94 / Finance and the Family: Allied-Lyons to change name - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
One of the biggest deals of this year was announced by drinks and foods
group Allied-Lyons, which is paying Pounds 740m for control of Pedro Domecq
group, the Spanish drinks producer. Allied is to finance the purchase with a
Pounds 651m rights issue, and plans to change its name to Allied Domecq,
dropping the name of J Lyons.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Allied-Lyons.
    Pedro Domecq.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
    ESZ  Spain, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P2082 Malt Beverages.
    P2085 Distilled and Blended Liquors.
</IN>
