<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Windfall prospects boost Gas
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN and CLARE GASCOIGNE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Anticipation of a big boost to revenues at British Gas saw heavy turnover
and a rally in the shares, which closed 6 up at 304p yesterday. Investors
were buying ahead of the expected windfall to the company from customers
paying early and beating the imposition of value added tax on gas bills.
Turnover rose to 18m, making it the most heavily traded Footsie stock in the
market. Volume was boosted by a block of 5m shares taken at 295p and placed
at 298p.
Dealers said the company had already received more than Pounds 100m in
advance payments and was expected to net around Pounds 500m ahead of the VAT
deadline at the end of the month. The effect will be to boost earnings by
about Pounds 30m, according to some analysts.
