FT  26 MAR 94 / International Company News: UAL in buy-out deal with unions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
UAL, the parent company of United Airlines, reached a final agreement with
its unions on a sale of 53 per cent of the company's stock to employees,
writes Martin Dickson in New York.
The Dollars 5bn buy-out, which makes UAL the largest employee-owned company
in the US, was agreed in principle last December, but hit a problem when the
company and unions failed to meet a deadline of March 15 for employee work
rule concessions.
