<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Frogmore jumps 74% to Pounds 7.3m in first
half
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Frogmore Estates, the property investment company, announced a 74 per cent
increase in pre-tax profits from Pounds 4.17m to Pounds 7.26m for the six
months to December, aided by increased rental income from acquisitions.
The company has built up its portfolio and has invested more than Pounds 70m
on properties since June 1993, when it announced a Pounds 42m rights issue.
Some Pounds 45m of this has been invested in trading properties, the
directors stated.
Activity has also picked up in Frogmore's joint venture housebuilding
business, which is expected to sell 700 units in the current year, compared
with 443 last time.
Turnover increased by 34 per cent from Pounds 22.2m to Pounds 29.7m while
operating profits rose 51 per cent to Pounds 9.62m (Pounds 6.35m).
The 1992 figure was held back by a Pounds 1.53m charge, related to
litigation. Without this distortion, operating profits would have risen 22
per cent, directors pointed out.
The interim dividend is 3.8p, compared with 3.6p.
Earnings per share were 13.4p (6.7p), helped by a reduced tax charge from
the release of earlier provisions.
Borrowings were Pounds 74.3m at December 31, representing gearing of 37 per
cent. Debt servicing cost Pounds 2.74m for the half year, compared with an
annual rent role that has grown to Pounds 24.4m.
</TEXT>
