<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Australian wool prices showed a very slight overall rise this week taking
the market indicator 4 cents up to 558 cents a kg., having touched 560 cents
on an intervening day. If anything the week ended a little softness among
finer merinos but not enough to disturb market sentiment unduly. Some
stockpile wools sold quite well in Melbourne, the first to be sold by
auction, with larger offerings next season a possibility. Australia is now
closed for auction purposes until after Easter. Business in wool textile
products generally is not as active as strength in wool markets indicates.
Prices are intensely competitive and stocks of tops are heavy enough to
prevent buyers from getting too concerned about rising prices. Only in the
carpet sector have developments led to pressures further down the trading
line.
