<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 94 / International Company News: Carolco to merge with retailer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Carolco, the troubled independent Hollywood film studio, is to merge with
the video and music retailer Live Entertainment in a stock-swap deal valued
at about Dollars 15m.
The two companies said the merger would create Hollywood's biggest
independent film production and video distribution company.
Carolco already owns more than a third of Live's stock. After the merger
Live shareholders will own between 22 per cent and 29 per cent of the new
company, to be called Carolco Entertainment.
Under the merger terms, one share of newly issued Live common stock will be
exchanged for 5.5 Carolco shares, but a 'collar' has been built into the
transaction that will keep the total value of the deal within certain limits
if the share prices of Carolco and Live fluctuate wildly before the merger
is completed.
The deal is the latest attempt by Carolco to survive a prolonged battle with
financial insolvency.
Although the studio has scored box office successes, rising debts, incurred
partly because of lavish spending on big-budget films, have threatened to
overwhelm it.
</TEXT>
