FT  25 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Enlarged TLS Pounds 209,000 in profit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TLS Range, the USM-traded vehicle rental group, continued to progress
through the second half and for the full 1993 year swung from losses of
Pounds 190,000 to profits of Pounds 209,000 pre-tax.
Turnover improved from Pounds 9.79m to Pounds 11.63m with acquisitions
during the year lifting the hire fleet by 1,318 vehicles to 3,056.
Earnings per share worked through at 0.9p (losses 0.98p) and the recommended
single dividend is being doubled to 0.5p.
Mr Peter Busby is joining the group as finance director effective from April
1. He was formerly with the Scapa Group.
</TEXT>
